how to resolve typescript issue with mongodb

I have an issue with this code

    const doc = await req.db
      .collection('clients')
      .find({}, { lName: 1, fName: 1, id: 1 })

giving the typescript error

Type error: Argument of type '{ lName: number; fName: number; id: number;  }' is not assignable to parameter of type 'FindOneOptions<any>'.

how can I fix this? thanks!
answer: @james - not as far as I know. The instant your rule takes priority, it overwrites (for lack of a better word) the bootstrap rule. You can't go back to bootstrap rule - the only thing you can do is have the bootstrap rule *again* to overwrite your rule (note you can however go back to CSS defaults)
